+        <p class="eyebrow">Clinical Attachment Programme</p>
+        <h1 id="faq-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
+        <p class="hero-lede">Key information for International Medical Graduates considering the NHS primary care observership at Hoyland Medical Practice.</p>
+      </div>
+    </section>
+
+    <section id="faqs" class="content-section section-alt">
+      <div class="container">
+        <div class="faq-grid">
+          <details open>
+            <summary>Is there an age requirement?</summary>
+            <p>Learners must be international medical graduates who graduated from a university listed in the World Directory of Medical Schools. There is no age requirement.</p>
+          </details>
+          <details>
+            <summary>Can I complete an attachment longer than 4 weeks?</summary>
+            <p>At present, the programme is offered as a 4-week NHS primary care observership.</p>
+          </details>
+          <details>
+            <summary>Do I need to be in the UK to apply?</summary>
+            <p>No. You can register interest from outside the UK, but you must ensure you have the necessary visa or right to visit the UK.</p>
+          </details>
+          <details>
+            <summary>Can Hoyland Medical Practice sponsor my visa?</summary>
+            <p>No. The practice cannot sponsor or assist with visa applications and cannot provide visa sponsorship letters.</p>
+          </details>
+          <details>
+            <summary>Is accommodation available?</summary>
+            <p>Accommodation is not provided, but the team can signpost candidates toward local accommodation options if needed.</p>
+          </details>
+          <details>
+            <summary>Do I need a DBS check?</summary>
+            <p>You may be asked to provide either a UK DBS certificate or an overseas police clearance certificate, with translation if required.</p>
+          </details>
+          <details>
+            <summary>Will I have a badge?</summary>
+            <p>Yes. On your first day, you will be issued a badge displaying your full name and position as a Clinical Observer.</p>
+          </details>
+          <details>
+            <summary>What is the dress code?</summary>
+            <p>Smart-casual and professional attire is recommended.</p>
+          </details>
+          <details>
+            <summary>Can I attend on weekends or evenings?</summary>
+            <p>No. Attachments are offered during primary care working hours, Monday-Friday, 08:00-18:00, on set cohort dates and excluding bank holidays.</p>
+          </details>
+          <details>
+            <summary>Why is the fee non-refundable?</summary>
+            <p>The fee covers administrative and placement-related costs. Fees are non-refundable once a place has been confirmed, but candidates can avail of another cohort in the next 12 months, subject to availability.</p>
+          </details>
+          <details>
+            <summary>Will I have an induction?</summary>
+            <p>Yes. Candidates receive an induction on the first day, including orientation to the practice, observer role and relevant governance requirements.</p>
+          </details>
+          <details>
+            <summary>Is there somewhere to buy lunch?</summary>
+            <p>You may bring a packed lunch. Nearby places to purchase lunch are available in Hoyland and the surrounding area.</p>
+          </details>
+          <details>
+            <summary>Will I receive a certificate?</summary>
+            <p>Yes. A certificate confirming attendance is provided after successful completion of the attachment.</p>
+          </details>
+          <details>
+            <summary>Can I complete audits during my attachment?</summary>
+            <p>Portfolio, audit or quality improvement exposure may be available depending on practice capacity and supervision.</p>
+          </details>
+          <details>
+            <summary>Will I receive a reference at the end?</summary>
+            <p>References are discretionary and depend on attendance, professionalism and performance during the programme. Completion does not guarantee a reference.</p>
+          </details>
+          <details>
+            <summary>I still have questions.</summary>
+            <p>Email <a href="mailto:syicb-barnsley.hoyland@nhs.net">syicb-barnsley.hoyland@nhs.net</a> for further queries.</p>
+          </details>
+        </div>
